## Why This Is Asked

To evaluate ability to design minimal-witness solvers for Horn-like rules and detect derivability with backtracking.

## Key Concepts

- Horn clauses
- Minimal witness extraction
- Forward-chaining with backtracking
- Cycle detection in derivations

## Code Example

```javascript
// simple forward-chaining for (A∧B)→C rules
function canDerive(target, base, rules){
  const derived = new Set(base);
  let changed = true;
  while (changed) {
    changed = false;
    for (const [A,B,C] of rules){
      if (derived.has(A) && derived.has(B) && !derived.has(C)){
        derived.add(C);
        changed = true;
      }
    }
  }
  return derived.has(target);
}
```

